<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="_smdTENoTEdmCj7Yn9Ev4rg" name="cots_produce_rfi,{02A195EA-D052-4ABB-9196-B5E2316AFBC7}" guid="_smdTENoTEdmCj7Yn9Ev4rg" version="7.1.0">
  <sections xmi:id="_tj-EMNoTEdmCj7Yn9Ev4rg" name=" Determine the Right Content " guid="_tj-EMNoTEdmCj7Yn9Ev4rg">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;DetermineRightContent&quot; name=&quot;DetermineRightContent&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The contents of the RFI should be written in such a way to ensure the information presented is clear, complete,&#xD;
    concise, unambiguous, and in an ordered manner.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It is essential that the Request For Information (RFI) is not a long and complex document. In order to gain the support&#xD;
    of the leading vendors to respond quickly to requests for information, it is essential that the RFI is kept to a&#xD;
    reasonable size and has a mechanism for easy and straightforward responses.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The RFI should not include detailed requirements. Detailed requirements are required to be signed-off, but it is not&#xD;
    important that they are signed off before you produce an RFI. Detailed requirements will be signed-off during the&#xD;
    elaboration phase as part of the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.cots/tasks/cots_define_solutions_10B95E6D.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{0970A6B8-349C-4C86-809B-AB025882F591}&quot;>Define Solution&lt;/a> and &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.cots/tasks/cots_recommend_solution_6C4FE964.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{74E63EE3-FA99-4409-A00D-CD863B1D6868}&quot;>Recommend Solution&lt;/a> tasks.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Consider the following when determining the contents of the RFI:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        An introduction section that specifies the purpose of the RFI and gives specific instructions for responding to the&#xD;
        RFI, such as number of copies needed, contact points, blank response forms or definition of response format, and&#xD;
        date for submission&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Information required from the vendors about the functionality of their products, indicating whether their products&#xD;
        can support specific high-level requirements, and whether the support is a standard feature of their product or&#xD;
        must be custom-built&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_tkEK0NoTEdmCj7Yn9Ev4rg" name=" Create Request For Information (RFI) " guid="_tkEK0NoTEdmCj7Yn9Ev4rg">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;CreateRequestForInformation&quot; name=&quot;CreateRequestForInformation&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Using the Request For Information (RFI) template, assemble the pieces of the RFI and gain concurrence from the&#xD;
    stakeholders on the contents of the RFI.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Note:&lt;/strong> A full description of the RFI is in the &lt;u>&lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.cots/workproducts/cots_rfi_7B50A891.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{5A422017-3ABA-4E8F-A564-D9A22F001FC7}&quot;>&lt;font color=&quot;#ff0000&quot;>Request For Information (RFI)&lt;/font>&lt;/a>&lt;/u>&#xD;
    artifact description.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;a id=&quot;Top&quot; name=&quot;Top&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To ensure that the information distributed to prospective vendors is presented in an ordered manner, that the&#xD;
        requirements are clearly stated, and that all vendors receive the same information on which to base their response&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        To create and send out a &lt;u>&lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../extend.cots/workproducts/cots_rfi_7B50A891.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{5A422017-3ABA-4E8F-A564-D9A22F001FC7}&quot;>&lt;font color=&quot;#FF0000&quot;>Request For Information (RFI)&lt;/font>&lt;/a>&lt;/u>&#xD;
        that will be used to gather preliminary information and assess a vendor and vendor offerings for potential &quot;fit&quot;&#xD;
        with the stakeholder's business requirements and candidate solution(s)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
